Reusable templates in GitLab CI/CD mean writing common job definitions once and reusing them across many jobs/projects. This reduces duplication and standardizes pipelines.

There are several common ways:

1. Hidden jobs + `extends`
2. YAML anchors
3. Shared included templates
4. Component templates for org-wide standards

---

# 1. Hidden Job + `extends` (Most Common)

A hidden job starts with `.` and acts as a template.

```yaml id="8thnq5"
stages:
  - build

.build_template:
  image: maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-17
  stage: build
  script:
    - mvn clean package

service-a-build:
  extends: .build_template

service-b-build:
  extends: .build_template
```

## Meaning

Both jobs reuse:

* same image
* same stage
* same build commands

Only job names differ.

---

# Real Use Case

20 Java microservices all use same build template.

One Maven version update changes all services.

---

# 2. Template + Override Some Values

```yaml id="x11v5k"
.test_template:
  stage: test
  script:
    - npm test

frontend-test:
  extends: .test_template
  image: node:20

backend-test:
  extends: .test_template
  image: node:18
```

## Meaning

Same test logic, different runtime versions.

---

# 3. Reusable Deploy Template

```yaml id="0a9r7j"
.deploy_template:
  stage: deploy
  script:
    - ./deploy.sh

deploy-dev:
  extends: .deploy_template
  environment: dev

deploy-prod:
  extends: .deploy_template
  environment: production
  when: manual
```

## Meaning

Same deployment logic, different environments.

---

# 4. YAML Anchors (Native YAML Reuse)

```yaml id="8cr2do"
.default_job: &default_job
  image: alpine:latest
  before_script:
    - echo "Starting job"

job1:
  <<: *default_job
  script:
    - echo "Build"

job2:
  <<: *default_job
  script:
    - echo "Test"
```

## Meaning

Reusable block copied into jobs.

---

# 5. Shared Template from Another File

```yaml id="8v0u93"
include:
  - local: ci/build-template.yml
```

Then in `ci/build-template.yml`

```yaml id="lj7lzc"
.build_template:
  script:
    - mvn clean package
```

Use in main file:

```yaml id="0s4q5p"
build:
  extends: .build_template
```

---

# 6. Organization-wide Central Template Repo

```yaml id="7yo6i5"
include:
  - project: devops/shared-ci
    file: java-template.yml
```

## Meaning

All teams reuse central standards:

* build jobs
* scans
* deploy patterns
* notifications

Very common in enterprises.

---

